## D-011 — Webflow staging strategy

**Date:** 2026-04-22
**Status:** Active

Marketing agents publish drafts using **Webflow’s built-in unpublished/draft state on the live site**. No separate staging Webflow site.

Rationale: separate staging site doubles Webflow cost, requires sync infra, and adds complexity. Marketing-HITL (D-010) is the safety net — content can’t go live without human approval anyway.

Implementation: `lib/webflow.ts` `publishDraft()` uses Webflow’s draft mode; `approvePublish()` calls Webflow’s publish endpoint after marketing-HITL approval.

