## D-013 — HITL escalation tiers

**Date:** 2026-04-22
**Status:** Active

|Tier     |SLA                                   |Triggers                                                                                        |
|---------|--------------------------------------|------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|Standard |4h                                    |General advice review, routine outbound                                                         |
|Urgent   |1h                                    |`escalation.urgent_deadline` (visa expires <72h, hearing within 7d)                             |
|Critical |15min business hours / paged off-hours|`escalation.adverse_notice` (denial received), `escalation.criminal_history` (intake disclosure)|
|Marketing|24h                                   |All marketing content (per D-010)                                                               |

Off-hours pager: critical-tier only. Pager rotation set per tenant.

Rationale: not all HITL queue items have the same time sensitivity; tiering prevents Sev-1 events from sitting behind routine drafts.

Implementation: `HITLApproval.tier` enum; `services/orchestrator.ts` sets tier based on `escalation.*` event; `/admin/approvals` UI sorts by tier.

